description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Respiratory Team at Wye Valley NHS Trust Hereford, who are looking for an Band 7 ANP/AHP to work on our busy Respiratory ward, which provides high quality care to patients with acute and chronic respiratory conditions. The post will be 19.5 hrs/week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant will work closely with the ward consultants, but will also be expected to work independently within their own scope of practice as well as in the team, whist developing and supporting junior colleagues.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be expected to be part of the 7 day medical working model (once initiated), working alongside consultants on call over weekends.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would also consider a Band 6 developmental role for the right candidate with the understanding that they would be upgraded to a Band 7 once they have obtained the Non -Medical prescribing Qualification. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit, please contact Julie Manning Lead Respiratory Nurse, on 01432 364416 or via email  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;julie.manning@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
